embeds.title: Sneaky Teakwood Match
embeds.description:
Common Relic / The Hexaghost / Downfall

At the start of each combat, **Ignite** the current Ghostflame and **Advance.**
*Lights on any surface!*

messages.content: consistency AND acceleration?
make go fast!
one of the biggest parts of playing hexaghost is making sure you have soulburn turn 1
this relic makes sure that happens, AND it brings you closer to the inferno

ALSO, you aren't forced to play two attacks turn one, opening a few more possibilities, so if you draw float and a skill turn one, you're suddenly on the bolstering flame with 2 active ghostflames, and then you play a power and you're already halfway to the inferno, your step throughs are gigantic on turn one
this relic is deceptively good, it gives you a lot more flexibility on turn one
this relic has a lot more value than just 4 soulburn, which is what a novice player might see this as looking from the outside in

It's a very good value relic, as are nearly all relics that improve your turn 1, since it's guarenteed to happen in every fight. This one is wonderful in particular because it makes sure that soulburn starts early so that it can detonate early, and speeds up the process of moving around/lighting the ghostflames by putting you on the 2nd one right away. As you get later into the run, it can also be difficult to draw/play 2 attacks in a turn, but playing 2 skills is usually much easier, making the process of moving around the ghostflames smoother as a whole. This definitely feels pretty strong for a common relic, moving to uncommon seems reasonable. I think you should basically always buy this at a shop when you see it unless you desperately need to remove a bad curse or buy a win condition card.
